    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What does ESG stand for?</summary>
        <p>ESG stands for Environmental, Social, and Governance. It's a framework used to evaluate a company's sustainability and ethical impact.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What makes a stock an ESG stock?</summary>
        <p>A stock is considered ESG if the company scores highly on criteria such as reducing carbon footprints, promoting workplace diversity, and maintaining transparent corporate governance.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do ESG stocks underperform the market?</summary>
        <p>Studies have shown mixed results, but many ESG funds perform competitively with traditional funds while offering lower downside risk during certain market conditions.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How can I find ESG stocks?</summary>
        <p>Many brokerages and independent research firms provide ESG ratings for individual stocks. You can also invest in specialized ESG ETFs or mutual funds.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is ESG investing just a trend?</summary>
        <p>ESG investing has seen massive growth and is increasingly becoming a core component of institutional investing strategies, indicating it is a long-term shift rather than a short-term trend.</p>
